title: Must-see: 'Price is Right' model takes a tumble, smashes set light
text:
Cox Media Group National Content Desk Must-see: 'Price is Right' model takes a tumble, smashes set light 6:12 a.m. Sunday, Oct. 25, 2015 | Filed in: Nation &World ï»¿ 
Come on down! 
Amber Lancaster, a model on the popular game show "The Price Is Right," is making headlines after she took a tumble on Friday's show, smashing a set light in the process. Video still via The The Price Is Right / YouTube 
Lancaster was cheering on contestant Leah, who was screaming and jumping with glee after guessing the price of an ATV in Double Prices. 
>> Read more trending stories 
After Lancaster stumbled in her heels and shattered the glass light bulb, Leah gasped. "Did I do that?" the contestant asked. 
Later, Leah turned to Lancaster and asked, "Are you OK?" Lancaster's response: "Yeah, I'm fine. I'm just gonna die of embarrassment."
